HEADWORD: Warison
<hw>War"i*son</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>warison</ets> safety, supplies, cure, F. <ets>gu⟦eacute⟧rison</ets>
cure. See <er>Warish</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Preparation; protection; provision; supply.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Reward; requital; guerdon.</def> <mark>[Obs. or
Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wit and wisdom is good <qex>warysoun</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Proverbs
of Hending.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wark</ent>⟦br⟧
